New York Governor Andrew Cuomo was joined Monday by governors of northeast states including New Jersey, Connecticut, Rhode Island, Pennsylvania, and Delaware to hold a briefing on the coronavirus pandemic and their ideas for a shared "reopening plan."



Yesterday, President Trump tweeted: "For the purpose of creating conflict and confusion, some in the Fake News Media are saying that it is the Governors decision to open up the states, not that of the President of the United States & the Federal Government."



"Working together makes the most sense...doing this methodically, but doing this now," Connecticut Gov. Ned Lamont said, calling for "establishing the same protocols" between the states.



